  "original_title": "\u0b85\u0bb0\u0b9a\u0bbe\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1 \u0b8e\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0bbe\u0b95 \u0bae\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd \u0bae\u0bc0\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0bc0\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc1\u0bb5\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bb3\u0bcd - \u0ba8\u0bbe\u0bb2\u0b95 \u0b95\u0bca\u0b9f\u0bb9\u0bc7\u0bb5\u0bbe \u0b8e\u0b9a\u0bcd\u0b9a\u0bb0\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bc8",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "People will take to the streets again against the government - Nalaka Godahewa warns",
      "author": "Digital Desk 5",
      "body_lines": [
        "The government has not yet taken any steps to address the basic problems facing the people of the country.",
        "If the problems are not resolved, people will protest against the government and take to the streets again, said Nalaka Godahewa, a Member of Parliament for the Sri Lanka People's Alliance.",
        "The main reason for the government's failure was the misunderstanding of the ideas put forward by many to form an all-party government to solve the problems.",
        "None of the key parties in the government, including the prime minister and ministers, comment on the country's problems.",
        "The president does not address the nation. If the issue is not addressed, the people of the country will once again take to the streets to protest against the government.",
        "We have stated that we will unconditionally support the resolutions of the government led by the Prime Minister Ranil Wickremesinghe, who is not a stable force in Parliament, in the interest of the country.",
        "Although the government has stated that it will pay close attention to the loss-making state-owned enterprises, including SriLankan Airlines and the Ceylon Petroleum Corporation, it has not been heeded.",
        "He said the government had not yet paid attention to the crisis situation in the supply of fuel and gas, power shortages and power outages, as well as the crisis faced by the people due to rising prices of essential commodities."
      ],
